>"How big should I leave the pieces for you? I usually like bigger pieces" you say as you saw through the steak
>"However you like will do" she says as she watches you 
>"There we go, all done" you say as you finish and slide the plate back to her with her fork
>"Thank you Anon" she says with the first genuine smile you've seen from her today
>You wave it off
>"Don't mention it, it’s no big deal"
>She’s quiet for a moment
>"It is to me, I haven't had the best of luck lately" she says frowning
>"Ah well we can't all have the best of dates, I had one where the girl I was with played on her phone the whole time" you say trying to avoid the whole...missing arm 
>She sighs
>"Yea my friend set me up on a blind date, said that it would be good for me to go out and socialize, I guess she didn't tell him I was a maned wolf or about Uhmm...this" she waves the stump of her left arm at you
>You grimace
>"Well his loss then, I mean I don't get a chance to have lunch with a pretty lady like yourself very often, so I guess I should thank him later" you say with a smile
>She laughs at that
>God her laugh is addictive to listen to
>"Aw you flatterer, thinking I'm pretty" she says with a smile, looking down at her plate
>"Well it’s true" you say before munching on a fry
>You both eat and chat 
>You learn little things about her
>She’s 27, works as a designer, enjoyed reading and sewing as hobbies
>You tell her you work as a web designer
