>You were happy you could share your stories
>You were happy you could be together like this
>She fades off to sleep and so you do, with visions of you two together for years to come

Chapter 5: Mourning Morning
>You had lost everything
>The wildfires had swept across states from California leaving fields of ash
>It took weeks to contain the fires
>You were standing in front of what used to be your apartment building
>You and Raquel had been evacuated, you literally only had a luggage bag of clothes and your car
>Raquel’s apartment building had been sparred but everything everywhere was covered in ash
>You kick a bit of burnt wood and sigh
>What now
>You had insurance on your things but that would take weeks to process
>Literally thousands of people had lost everything just like you
>"Anon? Come on babe, let’s go, we won’t be able to salvage anything" Raquel says putting her paw on your shoulder
>You stare up at fire scorched building and swear angrily to yourself
>Things were just going too well 
>You had just gotten a promotion, Raquel was getting more and more celebrities looking for her work
>And then life decided to kick you in the metaphorical balls again
>First you lose everything when you’re transported into this world
>Then you lose everything because California is a place where you could fart and the state would blow up and everything around it would burn
>You couldn’t even go back to Raquel’s place yet
>The area was under quarantine, the smoke and ash was heavily toxic after a few chemical plants burned down
>They said the cleanup could take weeks
>Your phone goes off, you look at the screen and frown slightly
>Jasmine the tiger was calling, it’s not that you disliked her, far from it
>She was friendly and nice and called you periodically seeing how you were
>She got you in contact with the people to help get your certificates and credentials back after you got transported here
>But you were in an sour mood and didn’t want to accidentally burn a bridge because of your temper
>You answer the call anyway
>"Hi Anon, how are you holding up, I hope those fires didn’t affect you too bad" she says with questioning tone
>Your frown deepens
>"Well I’m currently looking up at the charred remains of my apartment, so they did"
>You could almost hear her wince through the phone
>"Well Uhmm... what about your girlfriend? Could you stay with her?" she asks pensively
>"Toxic ash... her place is quarantined" you say as you reach over and hug Raquel briefly
>"Oh mhmmm....do you have anywhere to stay long term? Friends or fam....err your girlfriends family?" you know she’s doing her job but you really want to end this conversation
>"No we don’t" you answer grumpily
>"Ok well there is an Anonymous temporary shelter around there, let me make a few calls and see if I can get it open for you and your girlfriend" she says, you hear papers flipping in the background
>"Her name is Raquel by the way" you say with a slightly better tone
>"Oh ok! I’ll give you a call in a bit! Take care!" she says before she hangs up
>She’s a bit too cheerful for the mood you were in
>You look at Raquel and smile softly
>"Well we have some good news, that BHA Agent says there might be a temporary Anonymous shelter we can stay in until we're back on our feet" you say to her
>Her ears perk up a bit and she smiles
>"See, I told you things were going to get better" she says hugging you softly
>You get to your car and sit inside waiting
>Not like you could go anywhere else
>Your work office had burned down
>The restaurant where you met Raquel was extra crispy
>Your phone buzzes to life and you answer
>"Hey Anon! Good news! There is a Shelter you can go to in the next city, a BHA agent will meet you there with the keys!" Jasmine says happily "I'll text you the info!"
>"Thanks Jasmine" you say as you start up the car
>"Also can you send Me Raquel’s Info? I need it for your file" she says matter of factly 
>"Uhh I’ll give her the phone"
>Their conversation is short
>Phone number, address...Species
>By the time she hands your phone back to you, you had already gotten a text with the info
>You plug it into your GPS and get going
>The ride is quiet, you both were tired, 
>The evacuations, the busy shelters
>The traffic, the suspense from not knowing if you would return to your home or....nothing
>All of it lead to this
>You had stayed in one of these shelters before, little apartments, hotel room like suits with small kitchens and a few pots and pans
>Nothing fancy
>But you supposed you were better off than some... but that doesn’t make you feel better
>You park and there is a Man in a BHA uniform waiting
>"You’re Anon? Jasmine said you would be coming, here’s the keys, just drop them at the local office when you’re back on your feet"
>You enter the hotel like buildings front door with all of your possessions and with Raquel’s luggage
>Looking at the key, you see the number 114 engraved into it
>First floor at least
>"114 love, should be on this side" you say to Raquel as you follow the numbers
>You find it and unlock the door
>It’s basic
>A queen sized bed, a nightstand, a small TV, the kitchen was so small you doubted you could open the dishwasher the whole way
>But it was free and was a roof over your heads
>You collapse onto the bed, and Raquel follows suit
>"Fuck" you say softly
>"Fuck" she parrots
>You grab a hold of her paw
>She squeezes it gently
>"Well get through this"
>You always do

Chapter 6: on Melancholy Hill
>Things between you and Raquel had been...tense
>Not because you were mad at each other, you love each other
>The fires and loss of everything you own had actually brought you closer together
>The issue was that you were both cooped up in a single room with each other
>You had no outlets for your stress and too much spare time
>Your boss had gotten in contact with you and said the new office would be ready in a few months
>Raquel couldn’t get to her sewing machine because of the toxic ash
>You had bought a new TV and a laptop to get some stress away but you could only do so much
>Plus there were several other Anonymous members here that were affected by the fire
>Some alone, some had brought whole families
>Cabin fever was getting to you so decided...fuck it
>Vacation
>You weren’t losing vacation time so might as well right?
>Luckily you were smart and had saved all your important documents
>And because you were such a great guy, you saved it as a surprise
>You were currently driving to the airport
>Raquel was trying to get you to spoil the surprise by asking 20 questions
>Questions like "what’s around it" "what’s it known for?" and "do I know anyone there"
>To which you answered "Stuff" "things" and "no"
>You parked in the "long term" spot and unloaded the luggage
>"What gate are we?" 
>"A24, let’s go" you say as you look at the tickets, hiding them from her view
>She pouts
>"When do I get to know where we're going?" she asks slightly annoyed
>"Now" you say pointing up at the sign that says "Hawaiian Air" at the check in
>Her eyes go wide and her mouth drops open
>"HAWAII!?!" she yells happily as she jumps into your arms "HOW?!"
>"Yep Hawaii, I called in some favors" you say with a smile
>A certain Anonymous member was really well off and was letting you use his vacation house provided you make his business a website
>When you asked how he wanted it he said "I don’t care just don’t make it too annoying"
>Made your job easier
>"How Long?!" she says practically skipping up to the check out
>"A month, he said we could use it longer if we wanted since he wasn’t going to" 
>The whole process of getting through all the airport stuff was a breeze as Raquel happily danced around and talked about Hiking and swimming and snorkeling
>"Ooo we can go to one of those shows and I can see if I can get some inspiration for new designs!"
>She was ecstatic and that of course made you smile
>You loved seeing her happy like this
>Such a HUGE change from that first day you met her
>It was hard to see that same Maned wolf crying into her meal in the now happily chatting Maned wolf
>Or course you couldn’t complain about the change
>Boarding was easy and being the genius you were had reserved a window seat for Raquel
>You grip her hand softly as the plane takes off and close your eyes
>Might as well get some shut eye

>You're awoken by Raquel gently shaking you
>"Anon? Anon look there’s the island!" she says happily 
>You lean over her to look out the window and sure enough there it is
>A green jewel in a vast blue ocean
>The flight paths around Hawaii are actually pretty low only about 9000 feet compared to cruising at 32000
>She watches out the window as the plane lands and you try to wake up more
>"Did you sleep at all Raquel?" you ask her groggily 
>"No, I was too excited" she squeals happily
>You smile and rub yours eye
>The landing is uneventful and getting your luggage and a rental car was easy
>You followed your phones directions to the summer house 
>Pretty standard Vacation stuff
>As you pull up you're in awe of the view from the house
>You can see Diamond Head from here and the oceans beyond
>What did this dude have when he came? 
>It even has a full working shower for Anthros
>Raquel is already unpacking and listing things she wants to do
>"We have to see that pineapple plantation, and go to half moon bay and shark tooth beach!"
>You smile and start unpacking your things as well
>This was going to be a fun trip

>You and Raquel decided that today was a comfy relaxing day...not a sightseeing day
>So you found a beach that you and her could relax at and spend the day
>You were driving the rental car, windows down, sunglasses on, not caring
>You glance over at Raquel
>She’s wearing just her red bikini top and a Flowing white skirt 
>It took a while to convince her that she didn’t need to be self-conscious about her Missing arm
>"There are lots of amputees in the world, nothing to worry about" you said
>She’s humming happily to a song on the radio you didn’t recognize
>She had tried to get you to listen to some Anthro artists but most were pop music, which was one of the few things you and Raquel disagreed on, but didn’t let get in the way of your happiness together
>You breathe in the salty humid air and smile
>From what you saw of the islands mountains beaches it was almost as beautiful as Raquel
>Almost
>You park and get out and breathe deep
>God that salty sea air always smells great
>Raquel gets out and takes a few pictures of the beach and the sand
>You cover your face whenever she tries to snap your picture
>You aren’t vain enough to take selfies and dislike having your picture taken
>"Come on Anon! Please let me get pictures of you! How else will we remember this?" She pleads as you keep covering your face with random objects
>You sigh
>"Fine" you say reluctantly
>"YAY!" she pounces on you with a hug
>She snaps pictures as you both walk to the water
>Luckily this isn’t one of the "touristy" beaches so it wasn’t completely full
>You set up a beach blanket, an umbrella and a cooler full of beer, sandwiches and water
>You look out at the clear blue water, listen to the crashing of the waves and the cawing of gulls
>Paradise
>But it was only paradise because you were with Raquel
>She's taken off her skirt revealing her red bikini bottom
>You can’t help but stare as she runs off into the water laughing happily
>You follow and jump in after her
>You wade out to her and she hooks her arm around your waist as the water gently laps at both of you
>"I’m glad you’re here with me Anon"
>"And I’m glad you’re here with me"
>Yhe Gorillaz had it right after all
"~Look, if heaven had a VIP, this is it, white sand, blue sea"

>You were hiking through the jungles of Hawaii up some mountain that's name you couldn’t pronounce right
>But you heard there was a beautiful waterfall and pool at the top you could swim in
>Raquel was having a bit of a rough time though
>The trail was steep in some places and required handholds
>So being the gentleman you were, you would go first and find the easiest way up then help her with both encouraging words and the occasional helping hand
>You were sweating though and she was panting
>Humidity was killer here but you could tell the daily rain shower was coming
>Plus the hottest it ever got was 92 degrees Fahrenheit 
>"I love the outdoors! I love this it’s such a different kind of Hike!" Raquel says as she looks up at the canopy of the jungles
>"The air is clean and wet, the ground soft! You can even see those super colorful birds!"
>"Plus you don’t need to worry about bears or mountain lions" you say with a smile
>You take a drink of water from your bottle and offer it to Raquel, which she accepts happily
>"We should be nearing the top" you say looking at the mile markers
>You climb a bit further only to have your heart sink a little
>There’s a sheer wall about 12 feet tall
>You could climb it easy but....
>Raquel...
>You turn to her, expecting the worst but you’re actually surprised
>She has a look of stern determination
>"Fuck this wall! I’m not letting it ruin our day. HOLD MY BAG!"
>She hands her bag to you and throws herself at the wall like nothing you’ve seen in her before
>She’s about 2 feet front the top actually after that solid jump onto it
>But she’s stopped
>"Uhmm...Anon...Can you give me a boost?" she says over her shoulder
>You smile and drop the bags off then walk so you’re under her
>"What do you need me to do love?"
>"Uhmm. Push my right footpaws up, I can’t find a good foothold"
>You cup both your hand and push her footpaw up and continue to push until you can’t reach further
>You hear a bit of scrambling and then a triumphant yell
>You look up and See Raquel jumping around at the top
>"I did it! I did it!" 
>You smile and get the bags and throw them up to her one by one
>You start to climb and get to where she was stuck
>Fuck you can’t find a foothold either
>"Raquel can I get a hand?" you yell up
>You see her poke her head over the edge 
>"Sure love!" she says happily
>She lays down and extends her arm to yours
>You grab her wrist and she grabs yours
>"Ok... one...two...THREEEE" 
>She pulls you and you jump up until you can grab the edge and swing yourself up
>You roll over the edge panting, Raquel next to you doing the same
>You take her paw into yours and smile
>"I Love you Raquel" you say through pants
>"I love you too anon" She says with a toothy smile
>You couldn’t be prouder of her
>After catching your breath you both continue the hike until you make it to the springs
>A 30 foot waterfall crashes into a large clear pool of water
>"We made it!" Raquel says happily
>You hug her close and scratch between her ears gently
>You get a happy growl from her 
>"We sure did babe" you say as you kiss her 

>The past month has been amazing
>You got to do so much with Raquel
>Swimming, snorkeling, hiking
>You went everywhere on the island and a few other islands by again trading favors
>The Anonymous network reached everywhere it seems and favors for things were pretty commonplace
>You got to see the pineapple plantation, an aviary
>The USS Arizona... where one of your great grandfathers had died...in the other world
>That part hit you hard, the other world
>But Raquel was there to comfort you about it
>You were happy for that
>As you both flew home you knew that even if you were cooped up in a small room with her, you wouldn’t want to be anywhere else

Chapter 7: Undisclosed Desires
>Some time has passed since the fires destroyed your apartment and left you with nothing
>But you moved on with Raquel
>And moved in together
>You shared a small 2 bedroom townhouse now
>The 2nd bedroom was a workshop / office
>But none of that was important today
>You were sitting at the rebuilt diner you had met Raquel at
>She’s sitting across from you laughing and drinking her tea
>It’s like the maned wolf from before the accident and it filled your heart with Joy to see her again
>Of course she said it was all you that did it
>But you couldn’t take all the credit
>All you did was show her the way, it was her choice to follow it
>"Raquel I have a surprise for you" you say as she finishes her tea
>"What is with you and surprises? You always do...this..." her words trail off
>You look over your shoulder and see that the plan worked
>Her mother and father are sitting at the Table behind you
>They had had their muzzles and faces buried in newspapers, pretending to read them
>Well they might have been reading them
>"Anon...What. How? Why?"
>>"I called in some favors" you say smirking
>"But that’s not important"
>"This is" you fish a ring out of your pocket and present it to her
>Her paw is to her mouth her eyes wide
>You slide out of your chair and onto one knee in front of her
>"Raquel Silva, you’ve made the past year of my life better than ever before, and I would love to spend the rest of it with you"
>You hold the ring up to her
>"Will you marry me?"
>Tears of happiness run down her face
>"Yes! Yes Anon!"
>She holds out her paw and you slip the ring onto her ring pad
>The Diner erupts in applause as you stand up and kiss her
>Her father slides over his chair and so does her mother
>The elderly Maned wolf speaks in broken English but you understand
>"Anon he. Call us, tell of your accident and his love for you and for blessing"
>Her mother speaks now
>"Of course we say yes! He good man! And so handsome!"
>You feel yourself blush as she grabs you cheek with her paw
>"Mom! Stop it!" Raquel says swatting away her paw
>You can’t help but smile as she talks to her parents


Sometime later
>The wedding was amazing
>The A man commonly called "the Chickenman" was your best man and he had brought along Jasmine the tiger
>You swear you saw a tear in his eye but didn’t want to point it out though
>The honeymoon was more than amazing
>You took her to Japan and got to explore 
>She loved climbing My Fuji with you, going to the poke centers and seeing the full-sized Gundam in Tokyo
>Work was going great too
>You were now able to work from home to take care of Raquel
>Raquel still designed but there was a small hindrance
>You look over from your computer to see her struggling to bend down to grab something
>Her swollen belly was in the way
>She’s about 6 months pregnant at this point
>You smile and stand up and hug her from behind
>"Hey! I’m working! Stoppit!"
>"No" you answer simply as you rub her belly
>She swats you away with her prosthetic left paw
>"STOPPIT Lemme work you romantic weirdo! Go yell at the moon again or something and let me work!" she says shooing you away
>You couldn’t help but love this Maned wolf more and more everyday
>"Hey babe" you say as you sit back down and let her work
>"Whaaaaaatttt" she says with a sigh
>"Love you!"
>Her ears perk up
>"Love you too"

